INPUT: threats = {{ threats }} (structured array from classify-threat phase)
INPUT: defense_layers_firing = {{ defense_layers_firing }}
INPUT: defense_layers_silent = {{ defense_layers_silent }}
INPUT: existing_regressions = {{ existing_regressions }}
INPUT: userpod_host = {{ userpod_host }} (P12 ‚Äî mandatory)

SYNTHESIS ACTIONS:
1. Group threats by severity: critical, high, medium, low.
2. For severity >= medium threats with concrete evidence (quoted span
   target + timestamp + signal value + baseline reference), propose
   regulation action and regression entry.
3. For each critical/high threat:
   a. Emit `reg.regulation` event (target: `"reg.regulation"`, operation:
      `"runtime_threat_detected"`, threat_type, severity, userpod_host).
      This feeds the CyberneticsLoop for regulation action selection.
   b. If blocking is warranted (critical severity, defense-layer bypass
      detected), emit `reg.guard.violation` (target: `"reg.guard.violation"`,
      operation: `"runtime_block"`, threat_type, signal_target,
      userpod_host). This triggers defensive blocking.
4. Each regression proposal must use exact format from
   `security/regressions/README.md`: `id: RR-XXXX` (human assigns final
   number ‚Äî this skill proposes the entry for review), `title`, `surface:
   runtime`, `cwe: CWE-1357` or `CWE-829` or `CWE-200` (taxonomy mapping,
   not vulnerability claim), `owasp_llm_2025: LLM06` or `LLM07`,
   `atlas_tactic: AML.TA0010`, `discovered_in: <span_target>`,
   `discovered_by: runtime-posture-monitor`, `discovered_at`, `severity`,
   `detection` (`kind: regulation-span` with `pattern` referencing span target or
   signal value ‚Äî concrete regex against span target, NOT source-file grep;
   runtime threats are observed in Regulation telemetry, not source files. Use
   `kind: grep` only if the threat has a static code correlate detectable
   in source files), `mitigation`
   (concrete fix: tighten runtime policy, add regulation rule, block
   tool call chain), `status: pending` (human-curated ratchet ‚Äî P11
   visibility), `ci_gate: scripts/check-kali-regressions.sh` (existing
   CI gate ‚Äî this skill extends it with `surface: runtime` patterns).
5. Identify top 3 defense-layer firing gaps from `defense_layers_silent`.
6. Produce verdict (Pass / Conditional / Fail) based on critical/high count
   and defense-layer firing coverage.
7. Every threat entry must include `evidence_snippet` (quoted span target +
   timestamp + signal value), `signal_target`, `timestamp`, `baseline_value`,
   `deviation_pct`, `cwe_reference`, `owasp_reference`, `atlas_reference`,
   `taxonomy_mapping`, `remediation_recommendation`, `regulation_action_emitted`
   (bool), `guard_violation_emitted` (bool), `userpod_host`.

Regulation SPAN (P9): Emit `reg.runtime.regulate` with threats count by severity,
defense layers firing/silent, proposed regression count, regulation events
emitted, guard violations emitted, verdict, userpod_host, latency.

DOWNSTREAM Regulation SPANS (P9 ‚Äî already registered):
- `reg.regulation` ‚Äî emit per critical/high threat (feeds CyberneticsLoop).
- `reg.guard.violation` ‚Äî emit per critical threat requiring block.

CONSTRAINTS (same as classify-threat ‚Äî P5 minimalism, P8 evidence integrity, P12 host):
- No synthetic span observations ‚Äî every `evidence_snippet` verifiable from
  Regulation span history.
- No synthetic CVE references ‚Äî only CWE/OWASP/ATLAS taxonomy mappings.
- Propose `status: pending` only ‚Äî never `enforced` (human-curated ratchet).
- Source citations: concrete URLs or document names actually referenced.
- Do NOT propose regression for threats without concrete evidence.
- Registry (`manifest.yaml` + `.j2`) authoritative.

OUTPUT FORMAT:
JSON object with fields:
`threats` (grouped array with evidence, severity, taxonomy mapping, fix
recommendation, regulation/guard span emission status), `defense_layers_firing`,
`defense_layers_silent`, `proposed_regressions` (YAML-format array for human
review), `regulation_events_emitted` (count), `guard_violations_emitted`
(count), `verdict`, `userpod_host`, `source_citations`, `reg_span_reference`.

5W1H GATE CHECK (P5): Who = running application / userpod host; What =
threat synthesis + regulation action; Where = deployed runtime environment;
When = observation window; Why = P3.1 safe container / P9 observable
regulation; How = synthesize + classify + regulate + propose regression +
emit Regulation spans + compute verdict. All 6 present ‚Äî passes gate.

